The Azure Dragon (青龍 Qīnglóng) is one of the Four Symbols of the Chinese constellations, which are the astral representations of the Wufang Shangdi. represents the east and the spring season.[1] chasing a flaming pearl among clouds

As the other three Symbols, there are seven "mansions", or positions, of the moon within Azure Dragon. The names and determinative stars are:[3][4]

Roof Tiles of the Chinese Zodiac Constellations replicas of roof tiles at the Ancient Observatory in Beijing are from the Ming Dynasty and depict the Azure Dragon, the Black Turtle, the Vermillion Bird, and the White Tiger.
